.TH "ib_ud_header_init" 9 "ib_ud_header_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_ud_header_init \- Initialize UD header structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ib_ud_header_init
.BI "(int payload_bytes "  ","
.BI "int lrh_present "  ","
.BI "int eth_present "  ","
.BI "int vlan_present "  ","
.BI "int grh_present "  ","
.BI "int ip_version "  ","
.BI "int udp_present "  ","
.BI "int immediate_present "  ","
.BI "struct ib_ud_header *header "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "payload_bytes" 12
Length of packet payload
.IP "lrh_present" 12
specify if LRH is present
.IP "eth_present" 12
specify if Eth header is present
.IP "vlan_present" 12
packet is tagged vlan
.IP "grh_present" 12
GRH flag (if non-zero, GRH will be included)
.IP "ip_version" 12
if non-zero, IP header, V4 or V6, will be included
.IP "udp_present" 12
if non-zero, UDP header will be included
.IP "immediate_present" 12
specify if immediate data is present
.IP "header" 12
Structure to initialize
